<br>
There are classes that can kill us, even if we gate after stripping our buffs away.  Of course they've landed a huge dot on us and we can die safely at our bind spot, but we do die in the end.  <br>
<br>
In my opinion, you havnt experienced Everquest until you've played on a pvp server.  I'm not talking about the younger years mind you but level 45+.  Things get very interesting at lvl 55+ where people wear gear and know what they're doing.  Especially when you see those 4 buff's you rely on stripped away before you know what's happening.  When that happens your true worth as a wizard is tested.... Kill or be killed.<br>
